escapedText.description:
Prefer to use `id.unescapedText`. (Note: This is available only in services, not internally to the TypeScript compiler.)
Text of identifier, but if the identifier begins with two underscores, this will begin with three.

__String.description:
This represents a string whose leading underscore have been escaped by adding extra leading underscores.
The shape of this brand is rather unique compared to others we've used.
Instead of just an intersection of a string and an object, it is that union-ed
with an intersection of void and an object. This makes it wholly incompatible
with a normal string (which is good, it cannot be misused on assignment or on usage),
while still being comparable with a normal string via === (also good) and castable from a string.

singleQuote.description: Note: this is only set when synthesizing a node, not during parsing.

isArrayType.description: If true, then this type literal represents an *array* of its type.

isNameFirst.description: Whether the property name came before the type -- non-standard for JSDoc, but Typescript-like

JSDocAugmentsTag.description:
Note that `@extends` is a synonym of `@augments`.
Both tags are represented by this interface.

PropertyAccessEntityNameExpression.description: Brand for a PropertyAccessExpression which, like a QualifiedName, consists of a sequence of identifiers separated by do

resolvedPath.description:
Resolved path can be different from path property,
when file is included through project reference is mapped to its output instead of source
in that case resolvedPath = path to output file
path = input file's path

originalFileName.description:
Original file name that can be different from fileName,
when file is included through project reference is mapped to its output instead of source
in that case originalFileName = name of input file
fileName = output file's name

renamedDependencies.description: ES6 Map interface, only read methods included.

hasNoDefaultLib.description:
lib.d.ts should have a reference comment like

  /// <reference no-default-lib="true"/>

If any other file has this comment, it signals not to include lib.d.ts
because this containing file is intended to act as a default library.

unredirected.description:
Source file for the duplicate package. This will not be used by the Program,
but we need to keep this around so we can watch for changes in underlying.

ReadonlyMap<string>.description: ES6 Map interface, only read methods included.

reportsUnnecessary.description: May store more in future. For now, this will simply be `true` to indicate when a diagnostic is an unused-identifier diagnostic.

DiagnosticMessageChain.description:
A linked list of formatted diagnostic messages to be used as part of a multiline message.
It is built from the bottom up, leaving the head to be the "main" diagnostic.
While it seems that DiagnosticMessageChain is structurally similar to DiagnosticMessage,
the difference is that messages are all preformatted in DMC.

exportClause.description: Will not be assigned in the case of `export * from "foo";`

EndOfDeclarationMarker.description: Marks the end of transformed declaration to properly emit expor

CommaListExpression.description: A list of comma-separated expressions. This node is only created by transformations.

MergeDeclarationMarker.description: Marks the beginning of a merged transformed declaration.

isNameFirst.description: Whether the property name came before the type -- non-standard for JSDoc, but Typescript-like

moduleSpecifier.description: If this is not a StringLiteral it will be a grammar error.

ExportAssignment.description:
This is either an `export =` or an `export default` declaration.
Unless `isExportEquals` is set, this node was parsed as an `export default`.
